const e='---\ntitle: "Orders & Webhook API"\ndescription: "Create orders and receive payment callbacks via API"\n---\n\n# Orders & Webhook API\n\nAlthough APayShop provides a complete frontend shopping flow, if you wish to silently create an order in your own third-party system, or need to receive status notifications of successful order payments, you can refer to the interfaces in this chapter.\n\n## Create Guest Order\n\nAllows you to initiate a purchase request directly through the interface without requiring the user to register.\n\n`POST /api/orders/checkout`\n\n### Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  "productId": 1,\n  "email": "customer@example.com",\n  "payMethodId": 2,\n  "quantity": 1,\n  "metaData": {\n    "server_ip": "192.168.1.1" // Only required when purchasing a \'service\' type product and a form is configured in the backend\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Field Name    | Type   | Required | Description                                                                                        |\n| ------------- | ------ | -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `productId`   | number | Yes      | The ID of the product to purchase.                                                                 |\n| `email`       | string | Yes      | The customer\'s email address to receive fulfillment information.                                   |\n| `payMethodId` | number | Yes      | The ID of the selected payment gateway (can be obtained from `/api/payments`).                     |\n| `quantity`    | number | No       | The quantity to purchase, defaults to 1.                                                           |\n| `metaData`    | object | No       | Additional data, usually used for `service` type products to collect data filled in dynamic forms. |\n\n### Response Example\n\nUpon successful creation, the API will return a redirection link to the payment gateway (or checkout HTML code).\n\n```json\n{\n  "orderId": "ORD_123456789",\n  "checkoutUrl": "https://checkout.stripe.com/c/pay/cs_test_..."\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Payment Callback Sandbox Mechanism (Webhook Engine)\n\nAPayShop features an original **Dynamic Payment Routing and Webhook Engine**.\n\nIn order to avoid hardcoding the messy signature verification codes of dozens of payment gateways (such as Stripe, PayPal, Coinbase, WeChat Pay, etc.) in the main project, APayShop implements a Serverless-style callback mechanism:\n\n1. The pure text `callback.js` code corresponding to the gateway is stored in the `payment_methods` database table.\n2. When a third-party gateway sends a Webhook to our `/api/webhooks/[order_id]`.\n3. The system extracts the `order_id` and queries the payment channel used by the order.\n4. It fetches the corresponding `callback.js` and dynamically executes this code in a sandbox environment using the Node.js `vm` module.\n\n### Plugin Development Specification\n\nIf you need to write a new payment plugin yourself, your `callback.js` must return an object that complies with the following specifications so that the main system can help you update the order status and trigger automatic fulfillment:\n\n```javascript\n// Example of the required return object structure for callback.js:\nreturn {\n  isSignValid: true, // Whether the signature verification passed\n  orderId: "ORD_123456", // Local order ID\n  tradeNo: "ch_123abc", // Third-party gateway transaction number\n  status: "paid", // Final status: paid (success), pending (waiting), failed (failure)\n};\n```\n\nThis design allows you to modify payment logic at any time through the web editor in the backend, achieving true hot-swapping of payment gateways!\n';export{e as default};
//# sourceMappingURL=4.orders.mjs.map
